<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="62" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,1007]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,802,827]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pinkaew and Muadsub" authorityYear="2014" box="[568,633,803,827]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Sirindhornia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bifida">
<emphasis box="[568,633,803,827]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">bifida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
means ‘divided into two parts’ in Latin, referring to the sacculus which is distally separated from the valva.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
